  "commentary": "With SPX at 6578.04 sitting below the massive +42B gamma wall at 6600 and just above the -20B negative gamma at 6570, dealers are likely buying this dip as they're long gamma in PIN regime. The proximity to max negative gamma at 6570 means any break below triggers amplified selling from dealers, while the towering positive gamma walls from 6590-6600 act as strong magnets pulling price higher with mean-reverting action expected. Watch 6570 as the critical support—hold above keeps dealers buying dips toward the 6590-6600 resistance zone, but a break below flips dealers into selling mode down to 6560.\n\nBottom line: expect a bounce back toward 6590-6600 unless 6570 breaks, then watch out below.",
